Privacy Policy for 96编辑器-Document editor

Effective date: 2026-05-28
Last updated: 2026-05-28

Welcome to this App ("App"). We care about your privacy and personal information protection. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, store, share, and protect information when you use the App, and what rights you have.

Please read this policy carefully before using the App. By using the App, you acknowledge and agree to this policy.

Scope
This policy applies to features and services provided through this App (iOS client), including template management, document editing, snippet management, export/sharing, subscription purchase, and restore purchase.

If future features involve additional data processing, we will update this policy or provide separate in-app notice.

Information We Process
Based on the principle of data minimization, we only process information necessary to provide core functionality, including:

Content you create: template titles, document text, categories, snippets, and related metadata.
App preferences: dark mode, autosave, export format, language selection, VIP status, etc.
Subscription-related data: product identifiers, transaction status, entitlement status (via Apple StoreKit; no payment password).
Basic technical logs: limited diagnostics for stability and security troubleshooting.
We do not collect additional unrelated data without notice and legal basis.

Sources of Information
Information you actively enter while using the App.
Necessary technical data generated by system/device during usage.
Transaction status and receipts returned by Apple App Store / StoreKit.
How We Use Information
Provide core product functions (create/edit/save/search/export content).
Persist your local preferences and improve continuity of experience.
Manage subscription status (purchase/restore/entitlement checks).
Improve stability and user experience (debugging and diagnostics).
Comply with legal obligations, handle disputes, and protect security.
Legal Basis
Where applicable law requires a legal basis, our processing may rely on:

Performance of contract (providing requested app functions).
Compliance with legal obligations.
Legitimate interests (security, anti-abuse, stability), balanced with your rights.
Your consent, where required.
Local Storage and Cloud Processing
This App is primarily designed for local/offline use. Main business content (templates, documents, categories, snippets) is stored locally on your device by default.

Certain functions (such as subscription validation) rely on official Apple platform services and are governed by Apple’s rules and privacy practices.

Sharing, Transfer, and Disclosure
We do not sell, rent, or publicly disclose your personal information, except in the following situations:

With your explicit authorization or consent;
When required for subscription transaction processing via Apple services;
When required by applicable law, regulation, or valid legal request;
In merger/reorganization/asset transfer scenarios, where successor remains bound by equivalent privacy obligations.
Retention Period
We retain information only for as long as necessary for the purposes described in this policy:

User-created content: controlled by you and generally stored locally until deleted or app uninstalled.
Preferences: retained for service continuity until reset or app uninstall.
Diagnostic logs: retained only for necessary troubleshooting period, then deleted or anonymized.
Your Rights
Subject to applicable law, you may have rights to:

Access, correct, or delete information stored in the App;
Withdraw consent (without affecting prior lawful processing);
Stop using features or uninstall the App;
Submit inquiries, objections, or complaints about data processing.
Subscription and Payment Privacy
Subscription payment is processed by Apple App Store. We do not directly receive sensitive payment credentials (such as card numbers or payment passwords).

Pricing, currency, trial policy, renewal, and refund handling are subject to Apple purchase pages and Apple policies.

Security Measures
We implement reasonable safeguards (including minimized data processing, access controls, and diagnostics) to protect information against unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or loss.

However, no technical method can guarantee absolute security. Please keep your device secure and avoid using untrusted environments.

Minors
If you are under the age required by applicable law, please use this App under supervision of your parent or legal guardian. We do not intentionally collect unnecessary personal data from minors.

Cross-Border Processing
If cross-border processing is involved due to Apple platform infrastructure or legal compliance needs, we will take reasonable protective measures as required by applicable law.

Policy Updates
We may update this policy due to product evolution or legal changes. Updated versions will be posted in-app with updated date.
